1 Run doas nano /etc/apt/sources.list.d/debian-backports.sources
  Then if you want debian bookworm backports packages and kernels

  Types: deb deb-src
  URIs: http://deb.debian.org/debian
  Suites: bookworm-backports
  Components: main
  Enabled: yes
  Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg

  if you want debian trixie backports packages and kernels

  Types: deb deb-src
  URIs: http://deb.debian.org/debian
  Suites: trixie-backports
  Components: main
  Enabled: yes
  Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg

After this CTRL X Y ENTER

2 run doas apt update && doas apt upgrade -y -t bookworm-backports
  if trixie backports run doas apt update && doas apt upgrade -y -t trixie-backports
